rolldice
------------------------------------------
rolldice is just a simple program that rolls an amount of virtual dice of any
size. Well, technically, all the attributes of the dice can't exceed SHRT_MAX,
but I think it suffices for any normal FRPG.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libreadline7-7.0.3-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.36.1-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libreadline-devel-7.0.3-3
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/sstrickl/rolldice

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/sstrickl/rolldice/archive/v1.16.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rolldice-1.16-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rolldice-1.16-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rolldice-1.16-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rolldice-1.16-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rolldice)
  /usr/bin/rolldice.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rolldice.README
  /usr/share/doc/rolldice/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/rolldice/CREDITS
  /usr/share/doc/rolldice/Changelog
  /usr/share/doc/rolldice/README
  /usr/share/man/man6/rolldice.6.gz

